        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 1:52PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 152 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Badin Lake, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Badin Lake, Plyler, Badin, Denton, Richfield, New London,
Eldorado, Fish Tales Marina, and Whip-O-Will Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
